# A major [[bus stop]], one that serves as a [[transfer]] point between a large number of [[route]]s.
#* '''2000''', Lynda Barry, ''Cruddy'', Simon and Schuster, ISBN 0743212177, page 85,
#*: In the '''bus station''' the father handed me five dollars and pointed me to the lunch counter. "Get yourself something to eat." He went into the men's room...&nbsp;.
#* '''2002''', Ted Heller, ''Funnymen'', Simon and Schuster, ISBN 074324236X, page 66,
#*: We're in my car heading toward the '''bus station''' to get to New York.
#* '''2003''', Andy McNab, ''Liberation Day'', Simon and Schuster, ISBN 0743483332, page 273,
#*: The square was near the '''bus station''' in the new part of Antibes.

====Synonyms====
* [[bus depot]] (usually, for one bus operator).

====Usage notes====
Contrast {{term|train station}}, which can refer to ''any'' place — major or not — a train is supposed to stop to let passengers on and off.

